OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1772637082
OL,3,CTrial begins of man accused of rape
OL,4,Cfor which man was wrongly convicted
OL,6,FThe trial has begun of a man accused
OL,7,Fof raping a woman more than 20 years
OL,8,Fago which led to "a most terrible
OL,9,Fmiscarriage of justice".
OL,11,FPaul Quinn, 51, is on trial accused of
OL,12,Fattacking and raping a woman in
OL,13,FSalford in 2002 after new DNA evidence
OL,14,Fwas discovered.
OL,16,FHe has pleaded not guilty to rape,
OL,17,Fstrangulation and inflicting grievous
OL,18,Fbodily harm with intent.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1772637082
OL,3,CTrial begins of man accused of rape
OL,4,Cfor which man was wrongly convicted
OL,6,FAndrew Malkinson, 60, served more than
OL,7,F17 years in prison after he was
OL,8,Fwrongly convicted for the same
OL,9,Fincident. Prosecutors at Manchester
OL,10,FCrown Court told the jury his wrongful
OL,11,Fconviction was "a most terrible
OL,12,Fmiscarriage of justice, one of the
OL,13,Fworst there has been".
OL,15,FOpening the case for the prosecution,
OL,16,FJohn Price KC said a number of
OL,17,Fidentifications of Mr Malkinson,
OL,18,Fincluding by the alleged victim, were
OL,19,F"all honestly and genuinely made but..
OL,20,Fmistaken."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1772637082
OL,3,CTrial begins of man accused of rape
OL,4,Cfor which man was wrongly convicted
OL,6,FMr Price told the jury: "Evidence
OL,7,Fgathered in the second investigation,
OL,8,Fincluding, as I said, DNA evidence,
OL,9,Fand which will be put before you in
OL,10,Fthis trial, proves... that it was Paul
OL,11,FQuinn and not Andrew Malkinson who had
OL,12,Fattacked (the alleged victim) on July
OL,13,F19, 2003."
OL,15,FThe prosecution allege that the woman
OL,16,Fwas raped twice, rendered unconscious,
OL,17,Fand strangled by Quinn after he
OL,18,Ftracked her for "some time".
OL,26,@nD@YOUtD@JpmtD@]pnuD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1772637082
OL,3,CTrial begins of man accused of rape
OL,4,Cfor which man was wrongly convicted
OL,6,FIt's also alleged Quinn, then 29, took
OL,7,Fthe woman's phone so she could not
OL,8,Fcall for help.
OL,10,FMr Price told the jury that DNA
OL,11,Fmatching the profile of Quinn was
OL,12,F"found in more than one place, upon
OL,13,Fthe clothing and, directly and
OL,14,Findirectly, upon the body" of the
OL,15,Falleged victim.
OL,17,FMr Price told jurors: "There is no
OL,18,Falternative plausible explanation for
OL,19,Fhow this DNA could have been deposited
OL,20,Fwhere it was found, if not by the
OL,21,Fattacker, during the attack."
OL,26,@}D@]O]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1772637082
OL,3,CTrial begins of man accused of rape
OL,4,Cfor which man was wrongly convicted
OL,6,FQuinn now lives in Exeter, Devon, and
OL,7,F"strenuously" denied he was the
OL,8,Fattacker when he was interviewed by
OL,9,Fpolice on December 13, 2022. He has
OL,10,Fpleaded not guilty to all charges.
OL,12,FDuring the interview, Quinn said he
OL,13,Fdid not know the alleged victim, after
OL,14,Fbeing told her name and being shown a
OL,15,Fphoto of her.
OL,17,FLaying out the prosecution's timeline,
OL,18,FMr Price told jurors that a dog walker
OL,19,Fsaw a woman "in great distress" on
OL,20,FCleggs Lane before 6am on 19 July 2003
OL,21,Fin Little Hulton.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1772637082
OL,3,CTrial begins of man accused of rape
OL,4,Cfor which man was wrongly convicted
OL,6,FThe alleged victim told him she had
OL,7,Fbeen "attacked and raped". It happened
OL,8,Fin a "remote location" at the foot of
OL,9,Fan embankment, jurors heard.
OL,11,FThe witness said he saw "a lot of
OL,12,Fblood round her face" and that the
OL,13,Fleft side of her face was "swollen".
OL,15,FMr Price said: "In what the evidence
OL,16,Findicates must have been a prolonged
OL,17,Fassault, she had been subjected to
OL,18,Fsexual violence of the gravest kind."
OL,26,@wD@POUzD@eO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1772637082
OL,3,CTrial begins of man accused of rape
OL,4,Cfor which man was wrongly convicted
OL,6,FThe alleged victim would go on to pick
OL,7,FAndrew Malkinson, who was working as a
OL,8,Fsecurity guard, out of a line up and
OL,9,Fexpressed "100% confidence that she
OL,10,Fhad been correct in her
OL,11,Fidentification."
OL,13,FHe had been identified by police as a
OL,14,Fpotential suspect due to an earlier
OL,15,Funrelated incident, and was spoken to
OL,16,Fby officers a day after the alleged
OL,17,Frape of the victim.
OL,19,FFive days later, Andrew Malkinson
OL,20,Fhanded in his resignation and told his
OL,21,Fflatmate he was travelling to Holland.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1772637082
OL,3,CTrial begins of man accused of rape
OL,4,Cfor which man was wrongly convicted
OL,6,FMr Price said that "this sudden
OL,7,Fdeparture only added to suspicion" of
OL,8,FMr Malkinson.
OL,10,FPolice discovered that he had actually
OL,11,Ftravelled to a Salvation Army hostel
OL,12,Fin Grimsby. Officers attended Grimsby
OL,13,Fon 2 August and arrested him that
OL,14,Fmorning on suspicion of being the
OL,15,Fattacker.
OL,17,FHe was convicted on 10 February 2004
OL,18,Fand was handed a prison sentence.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
